            <thetext>If you have a look at qx.Mobile Theming or Form page, you can see that the RadioButton and Slider is rendered very blurry on Android 4.x devices.

As I discovered it is an Android bug which occurs, when a div element has no (text) content inside, which triggers CSS anti aliasing:

https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=61805

As a work around we should apply a transparent text dot inside of these div elements, to make sure Android enables anti aliasing.</thetext>
